after taking into account $110 million
of negative cash flow from the network.

1019
01:07:16,661 --> 01:07:20,206
It was clear the fat on the network
had to be flitched off.

1020
01:07:20,290 --> 01:07:23,543
Please note an increase in projected
initial programming revenues...

1021
01:07:23,626 --> 01:07:25,712
in the amount of $21 million...

1022
01:07:25,754 --> 01:07:29,424
due to the phenomenal success
of the "Howard Beale Show. "

1023
01:07:30,967 --> 01:07:35,680
I expect a positive cash flow
for the entire complex of 45 million...

1024
01:07:35,764 --> 01:07:38,016
achievable in this fiscal year...

1025
01:07:38,099 --> 01:07:40,685
a year, in short,
ahead of schedule.

1026
01:07:41,478 --> 01:07:43,521
Beyond that...

1027
01:07:43,605 --> 01:07:46,441
this network may be
the most significant profit center...

1028
01:07:46,483 --> 01:07:48,902
of the communications complex...

1029
01:07:48,943 --> 01:07:53,073
and based upon the projected rate
of return on invested capital...

1030
01:07:53,156 --> 01:07:56,993
and if merger is accomplished,
the communications complex...

1031
01:07:57,077 --> 01:08:01,414
may well become the towering
and most profitable center...

1032
01:08:01,456 --> 01:08:04,125
in the entire CCA empire.

1033
01:08:06,127 --> 01:08:09,464
I await your questions and comments.

1034
01:08:09,547 --> 01:08:11,049
Mr. Jensen?

1035
01:08:11,841 --> 01:08:14,928
Very good, Frank. Exemplary.
Keep it up.

1036
01:08:40,620 --> 01:08:43,123
Buy you a cup of coffee?

1037
01:08:44,791 --> 01:08:46,334
Hell, yes.

1038
01:08:47,377 --> 01:08:49,796
Do you have to get back
to the office?

1039
01:08:49,838 --> 01:08:52,173
Nothing that can't wait.

1040
01:09:04,644 --> 01:09:08,231
I drop down to the news studios
now and then...

1041
01:09:08,314 --> 01:09:10,400
and ask Howard Beale about you.

1042
01:09:10,483 --> 01:09:13,653
He says you're doing fine.
Are you?

1043
01:09:14,404 --> 01:09:16,489
Are you keeping busy?

1044
01:09:16,531 --> 01:09:18,324
In a fashion.

1045
01:09:18,408 --> 01:09:22,662
This is the third funeral
I've been to in two weeks.

1046
01:09:22,704 --> 01:09:27,542
I have two other friends in the hospital
whom I visit regularly.

1047
01:09:27,584 --> 01:09:30,795
I've been to a couple of christenings.

1048
01:09:30,879 --> 01:09:34,632
All my friends seem to be dying
or having grandchildren.

1049
01:09:35,675 --> 01:09:38,011
You should be a grandfather yourself
about now.

1050
01:09:38,053 --> 01:09:40,847
You have a pregnant daughter
in Seattle, don't you?

1051
01:09:40,930 --> 01:09:42,974
Any day now.

1052
01:09:43,058 --> 01:09:45,560
My wife's out there
for the occasion.

1053
01:09:49,981 --> 01:09:53,526
I've thought many times of calling you.

1054
01:09:55,362 --> 01:09:57,739
I wish you had.

1055
01:10:00,575 --> 01:10:04,788
I bumped into Sybil the Soothsayer
in the elevator last week.

1056
01:10:04,871 --> 01:10:07,832
I said, "You know, Sybil,
about four months ago...

1057
01:10:07,916 --> 01:10:12,253
you predicted I would get involved
with a craggy, middle-aged man.

1058
01:10:12,295 --> 01:10:15,965
So far, all that's happened
has been one many-splendored night.

1059
01:10:16,049 --> 01:10:19,386
I don't call that
getting involved. "

1060
01:10:19,427 --> 01:10:22,889
She said,
"Don't worry. You will. "

1061
01:10:25,767 --> 01:10:29,354
It was a many-splendored night,
wasn't it, Max?

1062
01:10:31,398 --> 01:10:33,191
Yes, it was.

1063
01:10:35,860 --> 01:10:38,154
Are we going to get involved?

1064
01:10:40,782 --> 01:10:44,828
Yes. I need to become involved
very much.

1065
01:10:46,079 --> 01:10:48,248
How about you?

1066
01:10:49,624 --> 01:10:52,585
I've reached for the phone to call you
a hundred times...

1067
01:10:52,669 --> 01:10:55,714
but I was sure you hated me for my part
in taking your news show away.

1068
01:10:57,549 --> 01:11:00,760
I probably did.
I don't know anymore.

1069
01:11:00,802 --> 01:11:05,849
All I know is,
I can't get you out of my mind.

1070
01:11:10,145 --> 01:11:12,814
Marty, I know what NBC offered them.

1071
01:11:12,897 --> 01:11:18,611
Go to 3.5, and I want an option
for a third run on all of them.

1072
01:11:18,653 --> 01:11:22,032
I'm in a big hurry, and you and Charlie
are supposed to be negotiating this.

1073
01:11:22,115 --> 01:11:24,159
Good-bye, good luck.
I'll see you Monday.

1074
01:11:27,746 --> 01:11:31,207
- Jimmy Caan's agent says absolutely nix.
- You can't win them all.

1075
01:11:31,291 --> 01:11:34,753
- Where can I reach you later today?
- You can't. I'll be gone all weekend.

1076
01:11:39,758 --> 01:11:44,679
NBC's offering 3.25 mil
per package of five James Bond movies...

1077
01:11:44,763 --> 01:11:47,807
and I think I'm gonna steal them
for 3.5...

1078
01:11:47,849 --> 01:11:49,976
with a third run.

1079
01:11:58,485 --> 01:12:00,653
I'm gonna stick the "Mao Tse-tung Hour"
in at 8:00...

1080
01:12:00,695 --> 01:12:05,325
because we're having a lot of trouble
selling the "Mao Tse-tung Hour. "

1081
01:12:14,084 --> 01:12:18,963
That "Mao Tse-tung Hour's" turning
into one big pain in the ass.

1082
01:12:20,048 --> 01:12:23,927
We're having heavy legal problems
with the federal government right now.

1083
01:12:25,345 --> 01:12:30,266
Two FBI guys turned up in Hackett's
office and served us with a subpoena.

1084
01:12:32,227 --> 01:12:36,481
They heard about our Flagstaff
bank rip-off film, and they want it.

1085
01:12:37,774 --> 01:12:40,443
Hackett told the FBI to fuck off.

1086
01:12:45,699 --> 01:12:47,617
We're getting around the FBI...

1087
01:12:47,701 --> 01:12:51,079
by doing the show in collaboration
with the news division.

1088
01:12:51,162 --> 01:12:53,456
We're standing on the First Amendment:
Freedom of the press...

1089
01:12:53,540 --> 01:12:56,001
and the right to protect our sources.

1090
01:12:56,084 --> 01:12:59,754
Walter thinks we can knock out
the misprision of felony charge.

1091
01:13:07,554 --> 01:13:10,890
But he says absolutely nix
on going to series.

1092
01:13:10,932 --> 01:13:16,229
They'll hit us with "conspiracy
with an inducement to commit a crime. "

1093
01:13:16,271 --> 01:13:18,398
Christ, it's cold in here.

1094
01:13:18,481 --> 01:13:23,069
We're paying these Ecumencial
Liberation Army nuts $10,000 a week...

1095
01:13:23,153 --> 01:13:26,656
in order to turn in authentic film
of their revolutionary activities.

1096
01:13:26,740 --> 01:13:30,785
That inconstitutes
"inducement to commit a crime"...

1097
01:13:30,869 --> 01:13:34,289
and Walter says we'll all wind up
in federal prison.

1098
01:13:35,290 --> 01:13:40,337
I said, "Walter,
let the federal government sue us.

1099
01:13:40,420 --> 01:13:42,714
We'll take them to the Supreme Court.

1100
01:13:42,797 --> 01:13:44,758
We'll be front page. "

1101
01:13:46,384 --> 01:13:49,220
The New York Times
and the Washington Post...

1102
01:13:49,304 --> 01:13:51,222
will write editorials.

1103
01:13:51,306 --> 01:13:55,727
We'll be front page for months.
We'll have more press than Watergate.

1104
01:13:55,810 --> 01:14:00,648
All I need is six weeks
federal litigation...

1105
01:14:00,690 --> 01:14:04,319
and the "Mao Tse-tung Hour" can start
carrying its own time slot.

1106
01:14:20,752 --> 01:14:24,631
What's really bugging me now
is my daytime programming.

1107
01:14:25,674 --> 01:14:28,343
NBC's got a lock on daytime...

1108
01:14:28,426 --> 01:14:31,137
with their lousy game shows...

1109
01:14:31,221 --> 01:14:33,807
and I'd like to bust them.

1110
01:14:33,890 --> 01:14:38,353
I'm thinking of doing
a homosexual soap opera. "The Dykes. "

1111
01:14:39,854 --> 01:14:42,565
The heartrending saga about a woman...

1112
01:14:42,649 --> 01:14:45,944
hopelessly in love
with her husband's mistress.

1113
01:14:46,027 --> 01:14:48,154
What do you think?

1114
01:14:59,249 --> 01:15:01,376
How long has it been going on?

1115
01:15:03,878 --> 01:15:05,463
A month.

1116
01:15:07,382 --> 01:15:10,635
I thought it was a transient thing,
blow over in a week.

1117
01:15:12,012 --> 01:15:17,017
I still pray to God
it's just a menopausal infatuation.

1118
01:15:18,560 --> 01:15:21,938
But it is an infatuation, Louise.

1119
01:15:23,565 --> 01:15:26,526
There's no sense in my saying
I won't see her again, because I will.

1120
01:15:31,573 --> 01:15:35,243
You want me to leave,
check into a hotel?

1121
01:15:38,246 --> 01:15:40,248
Do you love her?

1122
01:15:43,668 --> 01:15:45,879
I don't know how I feel.

1123
01:15:47,839 --> 01:15:51,551
I'm grateful I can feel anything.

1124
01:15:54,262 --> 01:15:56,264
I know I'm obsessed with her.

1125
01:15:58,767 --> 01:16:00,477
Then say it!

1126
01:16:01,478 --> 01:16:04,981
Don't keep telling me that
you're obsessed, you're infatuated!

1127
01:16:05,065 --> 01:16:07,525
Say that you're in love with her.

1128
01:16:10,153 --> 01:16:13,281
I'm in love with her.

1129
01:16:13,365 --> 01:16:17,786
Then get out! Go anywhere you want.
Go live with her, but don't come back!

1130
01:16:17,827 --> 01:16:22,415
Because after 25 years of building
a home and raising a family...

1131
01:16:22,499 --> 01:16:26,169
and all the senseless pain
that we have inflicted on each other...

1132
01:16:26,252 --> 01:16:29,631
I'm damned if I'll stand and have you
say you're in love with somebody else!

1133
01:16:31,299 --> 01:16:36,137
This isn't the convention weekend
with your secretary, is it?

1134
01:16:36,179 --> 01:16:40,517
Or some broad that you picked up
after three belts of booze.

1135
01:16:40,600 --> 01:16:43,395
This is your great winter romance,
isn't it?

1136
01:16:43,478 --> 01:16:47,607
Your last roar of passion before
you settle into your emeritus years.

1137
01:16:47,691 --> 01:16:50,777
Is that what's left for me?
Is that my share?

1138
01:16:50,860 --> 01:16:53,697
She gets the winter passion,
and I get the dotage?

1139
01:16:53,780 --> 01:16:57,367
Am I supposed to sit home
knitting and purling...

1140
01:16:57,450 --> 01:17:01,079
while you slink back
like some penitent drunk?

1141
01:17:01,162 --> 01:17:03,248
I'm your wife, damn it...

1142
01:17:03,331 --> 01:17:05,458
and if you can't work up
a winter passion for me...

1143
01:17:05,500 --> 01:17:08,712
the least I require
is respect and allegiance!

1144
01:17:21,141 --> 01:17:24,602
I hurt!
Don't you understand that?

1145
01:17:26,688 --> 01:17:29,733
I hurt badly!

1146
01:17:37,699 --> 01:17:40,035
Oh, say something for God's sake.

1147
01:17:49,794 --> 01:17:52,172
I've got nothing to say.

1148
01:18:02,766 --> 01:18:05,185
I won't give you up easily.

1149
01:18:11,608 --> 01:18:14,444
I think perhaps it is better
if you move out.

1150
01:18:20,200 --> 01:18:22,494
Does she love you?

1151
01:18:26,414 --> 01:18:30,210
I'm not sure she's capable
of any real feelings.

1152
01:18:30,251 --> 01:18:34,339
She's television generation.
She learned life from Bugs Bunny.

1153
01:18:34,422 --> 01:18:38,176
The only reality she knows
comes to her from over the TV set.

1154
01:18:40,011 --> 01:18:43,973
She's very carefully devised a number
of scenarios for all of us to play...

1155
01:18:44,057 --> 01:18:46,893
like a movie of the week.

1156
01:18:49,354 --> 01:18:52,273
My God, look at us.

1157
01:18:52,357 --> 01:18:55,652
Here we are going through
the obligatory middle-of-act-two...

1158
01:18:55,735 --> 01:18:59,698
"scorned wife throws
